    "summary": "I have more than two decades of experience in processing and interpreting Earth Observation data from multiple space-borne instruments to learn more about ocean circulation and climate. My special playground  has been the field of radar altimetry, spanning from the technical details of the instruments, through the algorithmic issues, to the use of data and exploitation of synergies with other measurement systems, over the open ocean and in the coastal zone. \nIn my more recent roles for the European Space Agency, first based at the Climate Office and now as an Ocean and Ice Senior Scientist in the Earth and Mission Science Division, I aim at enabling excellent science from current and future satellite missions. This contributes to the knowledge of how the Earth system works and how we are affecting it, and hopefully helps people understand that we need to adopt a sustainable behaviour.\n\nSpecialties: Remote sensing of Oceans and Climate\nSatellite Altimetry\nSignal processing in Satellite Oceanography\nCoastal Altimetry\n",
